diff:1670647457:1670033617:=52,66c52%0a%3c #foxbegin 221210-044418-462070#%0a%3c (:div1 class=expansionhead:)%0a%3c !!!Well-being of minority language speakers %0a%3c -> - nathandeyak%0a%3c -> [-09.12.2022 - 20:44-]%0a%3c >>rfloat%3c%3c   %0a%3c (:if1 authgroup @tas:)%0a%3c {[foxdelrange button 221210-044418-462070 {$FullName} ]}%0a%3c (:if1end:)%0a%3c >>%3c%3c%0a%3c (:div1end:) %0a%3c >>messageitem%3c%3c %0a%3c This is especially concerning because of the importance of quick, accurate, and comfortable in the hospital setting. If staff are unnecessarily forced to use a second language in a situation where their first suffices, this could cause issues where a condition is incorrectly communicated, or there is some delay while something is translated either externally or internally, and someone does not receive the help that they need.%0a%3c >>%3c%3c%0a%3c #foxend 221210-044418-462070#%0a---%0a> %0a
